@node Menus "WeatherExperience ∑†Usage - The Menus"
@{u}Usage - The Menus@{uu}
@{b}Project@{ub}
  @{b}Hide@{ub}
  Hide WE's userinterface.  You can use the MUI settings to configure whether
  WE should open an icon on the Workbench or be completely hidden.

  @{b}About...@{ub}
  Open the Aboutwindow with some information about WE.

  @{b}About MUI...@{ub}
  Open the MUI aboutwindow.

  @{b}Quit@{ub}
  Quit WE.

@{b}Weatherdata@{ub}
  @{b}Copy to clipboard@{ub}
  Copy weatherdata for selected cities to the clipboard.

  @{b}Print@{ub}
  Print weatherdata for selected cities.

  @{b}Save to disk...@{ub}
  Save weatherdata for selected cities to disk.  A filerequester will open,
  allowing you to choose a filename.  If you select a file which already
  exists, you will be asked whether you want to overwrite the file or append
  the data to the end of the file.

@{b}Settings@{ub}
  @{b}WeatherExperience...@{ub}
  Open the @{"WE Settingswindow" link SettingsWin}.

  @{b}MUI...@{ub}
  Open the @{"MUI" link MUI} Settingswindow.  Here you can configure exactly
  how you want the WE userinterface to look.
@endnode

@node MainWin "WeatherExperience ∑†Usage - The Main Window"
@{u}Usage - The Main Window@{uu}
The listview that dominates this window will show you the weatherdata for all
cities you have chosen to monitor. Doubleclick a city to open the @{"Forecastwindow" link ForecastWin}.
Multiselect cities and manipulate their data with the "Weatherdata/#?" 
@{"menuitems" link Menus}.

Weatherdata is shown in columns, and an entry of "N/A" means the data isn't
available from the server.

The small textfield shows you what WE is doing while refreshing weatherdata.

The @{b}Refresh@{ub} button contacts the weatherservers and updates the data in
the listview. The @{b}Abort@{ub} button aborts a refresh.

The window closegadget quits WE. (As opposed to hiding it, as in some 
commodities.)
@endnode

@node ForecastWin "WeatherExperience ∑†Usage - The Forecast Window"
@{u}Usage - The Forecast Window@{uu}
This window opens when you doubleclick a city in the @{"main window" link MainWin} listview.

Use the @{b}Copy to clipboard@{ub} to copy the forecast to the clipboard, or the
@{b}Print@{ub} button to print it.

Forecasts are sadly only available for US cities.
@endnode

@node SettingsWin "WeatherExperience ∑†Usage - The Settings Window"
@{u}Usage - The Settings Window@{uu}
The configuration of WE is split into three pages:

@{b}Cities@{ub}
Here you configure which cities you want WE to fetch weatherdata for.  Choose
a region from the popup window and drag cities from the left listview into
the right one.

Dragging is done by selecting a city in the listview and holding the left
mousebutton down while moving the mouse. 

Drag cities back into the left listview if you don't want to monitor them,
and rearrange cities within the right listview to determine in which order
they will be shown in the @{"main window" link MainWin} listview.

@{b}Fields@{ub}
WeatherExperience can display many different kinds of weatherdata about
cities.  Some are fetched raw from the servers and some are calculated based
on the raw data.  In this page you decide which of these fields of data shuld
be shown as columns in the main window listview.  You can also decide wich
order they should be shown in.

WE also has the ability to convert raw data between different units of
measuring.  Use the cyclegadgets below the listviews to decide which units WE
should use.

@{b}Network@{ub}
This page lets you enter new names of servers, should you know any I don't
know, and rearrange the order in which WE attempts to connect to these
servers (using drag and drop).

Below that you will find a slider which allows you to set how much time
should pass between each time WE contacts the weatherservers and updates the
weatherdata.  Drag the slider all the way to the left to turn off the
automatic updates completely.

Below the slider is a checkmark that detemines whether WE should update the
weatherdata immediatedly after startup or wait till the amount of time
specified above has passed.


Below the pages are three buttons.
@{b}Save@{ub}   - make the changes permanent
@{b}Use@{ub}    - use the changes until the next reboot
@{b}Cancel@{ub} - cancel all changes done
@endnode

